
Overview of noun scouring

The noun scouring has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (1) scouring -- (moving over territory to search for something; "scouring the entire area revealed nothing")
2. (1) scrub, scrubbing, scouring -- (the act of cleaning a surface by rubbing it with a brush and soap and water)

Overview of verb scour

The verb scour has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) scour -- (examine minutely; "The police scoured the country for the fugitive")
2. (1) scrub, scour -- (clean with hard rubbing; "She scrubbed his back")
